@startuml rig-sequence
title Stateless Reverse Proxy and Identity Broker for IRI Facility APIs\n(as implemented — see RIG-ROADMAP.md for what is still missing)

' Force a font that ships on every macOS/Linux/Windows JVM. Avoids the
' "Times font not available" Swing warning some renderers surface as an "error".
skinparam DefaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam DefaultMonospacedFontName "Menlo, Consolas, monospace"
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam noteFontSize 11
autonumber

actor Client

participant "Kong\n(OIDC / Globus)" as Kong
participant "Load Balancer" as LB

box "RIG Replica Pool — horizontally scalable, stateless"
participant "RIG Replica\n(/{facility}/{path:path})\n+ tracing.span" as RIG
database  "Facility Map +\nTier resolution\n(config.yaml)" as Map
participant "JWT Validator\n(JWKS, optional)" as JWTV
participant "Revocation Checker\n(jti blocklist)" as REV
participant "Identity Resolver\n(exchange → vault → passthrough)" as IDR
database  "Exchange-token cache\n(per-process, TTL)" as Cache
end box

participant "Redis blocklist /\nDNSBL zone" as RedisDNS
participant "Facility IdP\n(RFC 8693 endpoint)" as FacIdP
participant "Vault Backend\nKubernetes Secrets /\nAWS Secrets Manager /\nDocker map" as Vault
participant "External Policy Engine\n(optional)" as OPA
participant "Target Facility API" as Facility

== Inbound: Kong → LB → RIG ==

Client -> Kong : 1. Request /{facility}/...\nAuthorization: Bearer ...\nX-Project: ...\ntraceparent: ...
Kong -> Kong  : 2. Verify OIDC / Globus token\n(may consume Authorization;\nre-expose validated bearer\nas X-Access-Token)
Kong -> Kong  : 3. Inject X-Userinfo (b64 JSON of user)\n+ X-Forwarded-Host/Proto/Prefix
Kong -> LB    : 4. Forward verified request
LB   -> RIG   : 5. Route to any healthy replica

note over RIG, IDR
  RIG is **not** an IRI implementation.
  Each replica is stateless — scale by adding replicas.
  Every request runs inside an OpenTelemetry **rig.proxy** span
  that continues the inbound ``traceparent`` and is re-injected
  into the upstream request so the facility's tracing picks up.
end note

== Facility resolution ==

RIG -> Map : 6. Resolve {facility} + tier\n(resolve_tier())
alt Unknown facility
  Map -> RIG : 7. miss
  RIG -> RIG : 8. Audit deny\nreason=unknown_facility
  RIG --> LB : 9. **404 Not Found**
  LB --> Kong : 10.
  Kong --> Client : 11.
else Known facility
  Map -> RIG : 12. base_url, timeout,\ntier (1|2|3),\noptional token_exchange config
end

== Bearer normalisation + JWKS validation ==

RIG -> RIG : 13. Authorization fallback\nif Authorization absent but X-Access-Token present,\npromote it (Kong-OIDC plugin handoff)

opt jwt_validation.enabled
  RIG -> JWTV : 14. validate(authorization)
  alt Token invalid
    JWTV --> RIG : reason=token_expired | invalid_issuer\n| invalid_audience | invalid_signature\n| key_lookup_failed | decode_failed
    RIG -> RIG  : 15. Audit deny\nreason=token_invalid:<code>
    RIG --> Client : 16. **401** (or **302** to login URL\nif Accept: text/html and\nauth_redirect_login_url is set)
  else Token valid
    JWTV --> RIG : ok
  end
end

== Token revocation (RFC Section 2F) ==

opt revocation_redis_url or revocation_dnsbl_zone is set
  RIG -> REV : 17. is_revoked(jti)
  REV -> RedisDNS : 18a. SET? rig:blocklist:<jti>\n(Redis, fail-open)
  REV -> RedisDNS : 18b. TXT? sha256(jti).<dnsbl_zone>\n(DNSBL, 60s in-process cache)
  alt revoked
    REV --> RIG : 19. (true, "redis"|"dnsbl")
    RIG -> RIG  : 20. Audit deny\nreason=revoked:<source>
    RIG --> Client : 21. **401** (HTML/CLI differentiated)
  else clean
    REV --> RIG : ok
  end
end

== IP allowlist for non-MFA service tokens ==

opt service_account_allowed_cidrs is non-empty
  alt JWT amr lacks any recognised MFA value
    RIG -> RIG    : 22. resolve client IP\n(X-Forwarded-For first hop, else peer)
    alt IP not in any allowlist CIDR
      RIG -> RIG    : 23. Audit deny\nreason=service_token_outside_cidr
      RIG --> Client : 24. **403** (body: client_ip)
    end
  end
end

== Project-context cross-check (always on, ZT-REQ-04) ==

RIG -> RIG : 25. Decode JWT (no sig verify)\nextract sub, jti, amsc_project_context\nauth_time, amr, acr, idp

alt X-Project header AND claim disagree
  RIG -> RIG    : 26. Audit deny\nreason=project_mismatch
  RIG --> Client : 27. **403** (body: header_project, claim_project)
else Match or only one source
  RIG -> RIG : 28. effective project = header OR claim
end

alt tier == 3 AND no project (header or claim)
  RIG -> RIG    : 29. Audit deny\nreason=missing_project_for_tier3
  RIG --> Client : 30. **400** (body: hint to send X-Project)
end

== Identity resolution: exchange → vault → passthrough ==

RIG -> IDR : 31. resolve_identity(authorization, facility, project, ...)

note over IDR
  Returns ``(authorization, mechanism)``
  mechanism ∈ {exchange, vault, passthrough, none}
end note

opt Tier 2 — facility has token_exchange config
  IDR -> Cache : 32. cache.get(sub, facility, requested_scope)
  alt cache hit
    Cache --> IDR : 33. cached "Bearer ..."
    IDR --> RIG    : 34. (..., "exchange")
  else cache miss
    IDR -> FacIdP : 35. RFC 8693 POST\ngrant_type=token-exchange\nsubject_token=<bearer>\naudience=<override or client_id>\nscope=<requested_scope or absent>\ntimeout=token_exchange.timeout_seconds (default 5s)\nverify_tls per-call (one-off AsyncClient when False)
    alt Exchange success
      FacIdP --> IDR : 36. access_token
      IDR -> IDR    : 37. forbidden_scopes guard\n(reject over-broad downstream tokens)
      IDR -> Cache : 38. cache.set(...) TTL = exp − skew
      IDR --> RIG    : 39. (Bearer <swapped>, "exchange")
    else Failure / timeout / forbidden_scopes
      FacIdP --> IDR : 36. error / timeout
      IDR -> IDR     : 37. log → downgrade to Tier 3
    end
  end
end

opt Tier 3 — vault_backend set AND (sub + project) available
  IDR -> IDR : 40. auth_time freshness check\n(reject when older than vault_max_auth_age_seconds)
  IDR -> Vault : 41. lookup(user, project, facility)
  alt Hit
    Vault --> IDR : 42. facility credential
    IDR -> IDR    : 43. pool-detection fingerprint check\n(warn / deny on cross-user reuse)
    IDR -> IDR    : 44. emit ``rig.vault.binding`` audit\n(user, project, facility, sha256 fingerprint, backend)
    IDR --> RIG   : 45. (Bearer <vaulted>, "vault")
  else Miss / freshness failed / pool-deny
    Vault --> IDR : 42. None
    IDR -> IDR    : 43. log → fall through
  end
end

note right of IDR
  If both tiers above are
  inapplicable or fail:
  IDR returns
  (original_auth, "passthrough")
  — Tier 1 native pass-through
  for federated facilities.
end note

IDR --> RIG : 46. (resolved_auth, mechanism)

== Optional external policy engine ==

opt policy_engine_url is configured
  RIG -> OPA : 47. POST {user, facility, path, method}
  alt Allow
    OPA --> RIG : 48. allowed=true
  else Deny
    OPA --> RIG    : 48. allowed=false
    RIG -> RIG     : 49. Audit deny\nreason=policy
    RIG --> Client : 50. **403 Forbidden by policy**
  end
end

== Upstream request ==

RIG -> RIG : 51. filter hop-by-hop headers\npreserve X-Forwarded-Host/Proto/Prefix

note right of RIG #LightYellow
  Mandatory traceability (always injected):
  • X-AmSC-Trace-Id  = request_id (UUID)
  • X-AmSC-User      = sub (when known)
  • X-AmSC-Project   = effective project

  Session-freshness propagation (when JWT carries them):
  • X-AmSC-Auth-Time  (epoch seconds)
  • X-AmSC-Amr        (comma-joined)
  • X-AmSC-Acr
  • X-AmSC-Idp

  Resolution marker (set only when applicable):
  • X-AmSC-Exchange-Status: Completed   (mechanism = exchange)
  • X-AmSC-Exchange-Status: Vaulted     (mechanism = vault)

  Trace context:
  • traceparent / tracestate (TraceContextTextMapPropagator.inject)

  Authorization replaced with resolved_auth.
end note

RIG -> Facility : 52. Stream request\n(method, path, query, headers, body)\nshared httpx.AsyncClient (HTTP/2, conn pool)

note over RIG, Facility
  Body is **streamed**, not buffered.
  RIG never inspects the payload.
  Per-facility timeout from config.
end note

alt Upstream success
  Facility --> RIG : 53. status, headers, streamed body
else httpx.TimeoutException
  RIG -> RIG     : 53. Audit error\nreason=upstream_timeout
  RIG --> Client : 54. **504 Gateway Timeout**
else httpx.ConnectError
  RIG -> RIG     : 53. Audit error\nreason=upstream_connect
  RIG --> Client : 54. **502 Bad Gateway**
else Other exception
  RIG -> RIG     : 53. Audit error\nreason=upstream_exception
  RIG --> Client : 54. **502 Upstream error**
end

== Response back to Client ==

RIG -> RIG : 55. filter hop-by-hop\ninject X-Request-Id\ninject X-Upstream-Latency-Ms
RIG -> RIG : 56. **Audit allow**\n{decision, status, facility, tier, sub, jti, project,\n method, path, latency_ms, resolution_mechanism,\n trace_id, span_id}
RIG --> LB    : 57. Stream upstream response
LB  --> Kong  : 58.
Kong --> Client : 59. Final status, headers, body

@enduml
